  <h3> Examine Contents of Session Database </h3>
  <ptext>
    <synopsis list-sessions [-f session-db] [-s | --short] [session-id ...]>

    <code>list-sessions</code> displays the contents of the session
    database, either all of the records, or only those specified by
    <var session-id>s, in a verbose format (the default), or in a short
    format.

    To query a session database which is not stored in the usual location,
    you give the <code>-f <i>FILENAME</i></code> argument, where
    <code><i>FILENAME</i></code> is the path to the file containing the
    session database.

    Note that the session database (usually in <code>/tmp/sessions.db</code>)
    is normally only readable by the superuser.  In this case, you should
    run this command as the superuser.

